Jotunn: The Unicronian Minions were never weak. Razorwing, you should
not have-

Razorwing: Doubted it, I suppose? I did not. I sent a WARSHIP! My best
troops were there, and they were neutralized before they could even
act! They are tough, yes, but they are few. What do you suggest, Jotunn?

Jotunn took on a proud figure.

Jotunn: I will crush them all! Give me full command of the
Governmental armies and I will make them regret the belly of their
damned master!

--- In nbwrpg@yahoogroups.com, "Airly" <airly2002@h...> wrote:
> Spire:
> 
> "Don't be so harsh, Jottunn, darling"said Lady spire with a
smile"When was the last time that we faced those Unicronians???? I can
bet that Razorwing didn't expect that they were tougher than last
time... I wonder if all those time they have waitting for reforces...
or they have reforces among the lost ones..."

>   Before the Maximal Lord could reply anything, someone intervened.
> 
>   Jotunn: She is right, Razorwing. Why have you kept the fun for
>   yourself? The destruction of the orbital is now your fault...
> 
>   Jotunn's massive form was standing in the doorway as it closed. He
>   moved a bit towards the table.
> 
>   Jotunn: So? What do you say?
> 
>   Razorwing gave him a piercing gaze and invited them both to sit down.
> 
>   Razorwing: I did what had to be done. What did you do? Did you even
>   have ships to send your troops?
> 
>   Jotunn clenched his jaw, but said nothing, then turned to Spire.
